# ConsentTheater website — local-dev secrets template
#
# Copy this file to `.dev.vars` (gitignored) and fill in real values.
# Wrangler reads `.dev.vars` automatically when you run `wrangler dev`,
# making the values available to the Worker via `c.env.*`.
#
# Astro itself does NOT read this file — these are runtime secrets for
# the Cloudflare Worker, not build-time vars for the static site.
#
# In production, set the same keys via `wrangler secret put`:
#
#   wrangler secret put CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID
#   wrangler secret put CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN
#
# Until both are set, /api/stats returns 503 with an empty result and
# the /stats/ page renders in "not yet wired up" mode without crashing.
# /api/event always works as long as the ANALYTICS binding is present.

# Cloudflare account that owns the Analytics Engine dataset.
# 32-char hex, found in Cloudflare dashboard sidebar.
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=

# Cloudflare API token with Account Analytics READ scope, used by
# /api/stats to query the Analytics Engine SQL endpoint.
# Create under Profile -> API Tokens -> Create Custom Token.
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
